{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"d4eb9eb05c8e7e760e59ab8c578fae019321a3fc"},"timestamp":1481634102,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxOTUyNDczNzg=","github-url":"https://github.com/geometry-zsh/geometry/issues/60","origin":"github"},"title":"Lag and high CPU usage on large repositories holding enter-key","message":"On this particular scenario, where the user holds the enter-key and the current directory is a huge repository, geometry (async library, in fact) may consume a lot of CPU and for this reason the prompt may \"lag\" and seem \"slow\".\n\nI attribute the high CPU usage to the [exec, kill, and re-exec](https://github.com/frmendes/geometry/blob/master/lib/async.zsh#L17) of git subprocesses to print the git built-in plugin.\n\nWe could solve this by performing a small cache (1 sec, half a sec) of rprompt. Any other idea? Suggestion?","files":null}]}